        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12193",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Constistency... all functions have (almost) the same functionality\n\nAnd correct results are not easy to mention if you dont have good date\/time knowledge. Even I sometimes switch things, but reviewing the result all comes clear.\n\nExample:\n\ngetIso supports $gmt:\nSetting GMT = TRUE will only have an effect if timestamp and timezone are closely together\n\nTimezone+2, Timestamp 31.12.1999 23:00:00\nwill have a result of\ngetIso(TRUE); -> 01.01.2000 01:00:00 +0200\n\nYou see in this situation the day, month, year, and hour are switching.\nIn most situations the useage of $gmt should be avoided if the user does not know how it works... \nAll functions were set to a default behaviour of GMT the user expexts.\n\nIn general the useage of GMT aviods the coding of following:\n\n$myzone = $date->getTimeZone();\n$date->setTimeZone('GMT');\n$date->getIso();\n$date->setTimeZone($myzone);\n\nHope this makes things a little bit clearer.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-10T10:00:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-10T10:00:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12205",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Object support was added to _week, _month, _year, etc. in a previous changeset.\n\nThus, $gmt now makes sense for certain situations involving methods calling _week, _month, _year, etc.  When an ambiguous date or date part is provided to one of these methods, a timezone is needed to disambiguate the date \/ date part.  For other values, such as a week number (e.g. the 3rd week of the year), the day of the week actually depends on the timezone, even though the timestamp (GMT\/UTC) is the same.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-12T15:39:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-12T15:39:26.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12206",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The new patch, coming soon, for adding explicit timezone support and removing the $gmt parameter should resolve this issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-12T15:40:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-12T15:40:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12216",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The latest API change excluded GMT from all functions.\nThe new behaviour is like\n\n{code}\n$date = new Zend_Date();\n$date->setTimeZone('Europe\/Vienna');\n$date->set('10:20:00');\n{code}\n\nRelated to $locale.\n$locale is used for \n\n* Parsing localized input\n* Creating localized output\n* Creating\/Copying a locale object with another locale than the original\n\n{code}\n$date = new Zend_Date('de_AT');\n$date->setTimeZone('Europe\/Vienna');\n$date->set('J\u00e4nner', Zend_Date::MONTH);\n$date->set('May', Zend_Date::MONTH, 'en');\nprint \"\\n\".$date->toString('MMMM');\nprint \"\\n\".$date->toString('MMMM', 'en');\n$newone = $date->copy('en');\nprint \"\\n\".$newone->toString('MMMM');\n{code}\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-13T13:13:42.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-13T13:13:42.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12217",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The new API which was intruduced with SVN 2717 extracted GMT from all functions.\nSo this issue is no longer raising.\n\nFor further information see ZF-744",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-13T13:22:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-13T13:22:28.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
